web-payments.FAQ_QUESTION_3: What happens if my payment fails?
web-payments.FAQ_QUESTION_4: How can I watch the game after purchase?
web-payments.FAQ_QUESTION_5: Where can I watch the game?
web-payments.FAQ_RESPONSE_1:
You can pay for matches with different methods, including:
  • Credit/Debit card
  • Paypal
Supported payment methods may vary per country or region.
web-payments.FAQ_RESPONSE_2: Our policy is to issue refunds if you could not access the match for a technical reason. Please use the contact form via the Help Center and Support icon to provide our customer care team with a brief description of your issue and your refund request will be handled accordingly.
web-payments.FAQ_RESPONSE_3:
Make sure your payment method has sufficient funds, and is:
  • Registered in the same country to your OneFootball account or the supported countries to watch the match.
  • Not expired or cancelled.
  • Enabled for foreign, secure online, and recurring purchases. Look for these settings in your banks mobile app.
Also, make sure your bank or payment provider has your correct details. They may need to verify your identity for security, e.g. with a password, PIN, fingerprint, or code sent to your device.

Still not working?
  • Try entering your payment details again using a private/incognito window.
  • Try a different payment method.
  • Get in touch with your payment provider.
web-payments.FAQ_RESPONSE_4:
• On mobile, all PPV live matches can be watched.
  • On web, selected PPV matches can be watched.*
  • via AirPlay or Chromecast, selected PPV can be casted.*
* Restrictions apply.
web-payments.FAQ_RESPONSE_5: Due to licensing restrictions, a match can only be watched in the supported countries or regions listed in the details section for each match. Please check this information before purchasing or review it in your purchase details.
